<section>
  <title><xref ref="S_directproof"></xref></title>
  <subsection>
    <title><xref ref="pr_divisors"></xref></title>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          For each example in Part (1),
          the integer <m>a</m> divides the sum <m>b + c</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Conjecture: For all integers <m>a</m>, <m>b</m>,
          and <m>c</m> with <m>a \ne 0</m>,
          if <m>a</m> divides <m>b</m> and <m>a</m> divides <m>c</m>,
          then <m>a</m> divides <m>b + c</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          A Know-show table for a proof of the conjecture in Part (3).
          <tabular>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><em>Step</em></cell>
              <cell><em>Know</em></cell>
              <cell><em>Reason</em></cell>
            </row>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>P</m></cell>
              <cell><m>a \mid b</m> and <m>a \mid c</m></cell>
              <cell>Hypothesis</cell>
            </row>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>P1</m></cell>
              <cell><m>\left( {\exists s \in \mathbb{Z}} \right)\left( {b = a \cdot s} \right)</m> <m>\left( {\exists t \in \mathbb{Z}} \right)\left( {c = a \cdot t} \right)</m></cell>
              <cell>Definition of
                <q>divides</q>
              </cell>
            </row>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>P2</m></cell>
              <cell><m>b + c = as + at</m></cell>
              <cell>Substituting for <m>b</m> and <m>c</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>P3</m></cell>
              <cell><m>b + c = a\left( {s + t} \right)</m></cell>
              <cell>Distributive property</cell>
            </row>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
              <cell></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>Q1</m></cell>
